          <div>
            <h3>Service-based Architecture</h3>

            <p>New mobile and wireless systems were designed from the ground up instead of adapting to previous generations. Previous generations were all built on top of the previous generation. Architecture is a Service-based Architecture with crucial components:</p>

            <ul>
              <li>Authentication Server.</li>
              <li>Policy Control.</li>
              <li>Network Slice Selection.</li>
              <li>Session Management.</li>
              <li>User plane.</li>
              <li>Access and Mobility Management.</li>
              <li>Unified Data Management.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3>Application</h3>

            <p>Wireless technology uses electromagnetic waves, such as radio waves, to transmit data and information without needing physical connections, such as cables. This technology has become increasingly prevalent in recent years, with a wide range of devices using wireless technology to <a href="/communications-expert-witness/network-communications-expert-witness/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">communicate data and information</a>.</p>

            <p>Wireless technology has many advantages over wired technology, such as increased flexibility and mobility and reduced cost and installation time. It makes it possible to connect devices over long distances without needing physical connections, which can be expensive and time-consuming to install. In addition, wireless technology allows for the creation of networks that can easily be expanded and modified, making it ideal for a wide range of applications.</p>
          </div>
